Secrets of War: Vietnam: A War Unwanted

War Documentary hosted by Charlton Heston, published by Mill Creek in 2013 - English narration


Information
------------------------------

Secrets of War: Vietnam: A War Unwanted
The Missions and Mysteries of the Vietnam War - Ignited and Exposed!
Discover the most daring covert operations, ingenious spy gadgets and cunning military deceptions that forever changed the course of history! From the Viet Cong s secret methods to hidden supply highways, underground cities, covert camps and double agents, this instant classic reveals a wealth of undercover tactics used by the American and Vietnamese military leaders during the controversial war. Narrated by OscarÃ‚Â® Award winner Charlton Heston this series brings to life the hidden and unique conflicts of Vietnam that were once declared classified information. Through rare archival footage, formerly classified documents and messages, coupled with interviews with experts, authors and eyewitnesses from all over the world this series offers the most historically accurate storytelling and re-enactments. Strong, specific and factual, Secrets of War exposes the real stories of the Vietnam War!


1)  Alpha Strike 
Exclusive interviews with North Vietnamese veterans, secret American operations in Laos and Cambodia, and the Navy's classified program to counter heavy losses against Vietnamese pilots...

2)  Hidden in Plain Sight 
From the Ho Chi Minh trail to the tunnels of Cu Chi, the remarkable story of hidden supply highways, underground cities, covert camps and double agents...

3)  Special Operations 
The stories of clandestine operational groups, their missions and mysterious means of survival...

4)  Johnsons Battleground 
Secret Vietnamese strategies were designed to sabotage American morale, while Lyndon Johnson's White House attempted to keep the support of U.S. citizens...

5)  Ho Chi Minhs Revolution 
The secrets behind Ho Chi Minh's control of Vietnam and his ability to force the Japanese, the French and the Americans out of his country during his three decade reign...

